-- Colombian Stocks: Petrominerales, Carvajal Empaques, Rubiales
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-06-04T21:35:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-04/colombian-stocks-petrominerales-carvajal-empaques-rubiales.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  dropped 0.6 percent to 14,041.42, while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  decreased 1 percent to 1,664.04.  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMG)  , a Calgary-based  oil company 
that operates in the Andean region, dropped 0.2 percent to
22,760 pesos. The company agreed to buy the remaining 20 percent
working interest of three Peru blocks from Veraz Petroleum Ltd.
for $5 million, payable in common shares of Petrominerales,
according to a press statement. The transaction is expected to
close in late July, according to the statement.  Carvajal Empaques SA (PFCARPAK)  , the packaging unit of
Colombian holding company Carvajal SA, dropped 2.5 percent to
5,170 pesos in its first day of trading. Carvajal Empaques
raised about 195.8 billion pesos ($107.7 million) in its initial
public offering, according to a May 29 regulatory filing. The
company was seeking to raise as much as 212 billion pesos,
according to a May 2 regulatory filing.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , which operates
Colombiaâ€™s largest oil field, rose 0.5 percent to 44,600 pesos
as crude rose for the first time in five days in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
